                    <comment id="12916088" author="mikemccand" created="Wed, 29 Sep 2010 10:55:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Fun fun... yes SimpleText uses MUCH more disk space than Standard &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.gif&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Though, this test tries to be relative, ie it&apos;s comparing disk usage of SimpleText before and after... I&apos;ll dig...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12917163" author="simonw" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 07:04:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;mike what was the solution to this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12917171" author="mikemccand" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 10:20:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The solution was to make sure RIWC did not enable reader pooling, because that can cause IW to use (at peak) more than the expected amount of disk space.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13013344" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 16:50:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 3.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
